$ Script: ff_ftp.bat

`ff_ftp.bat` is a → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/batch-file[`cmd.exe` batch file] that opens a → development/web/browser/Firefox browser with a `ftp://` url and a username-password tuple.

The username, → development/security/password[password] and host need to be stored in the
→ Windows/development/environment-variables[environment variables] `tq84_XYZ_ftp_user`, `tq84_XYZ_ftp_pw` and `tq84_XYZ_ftp_host`, respectively.
-
When the script is called, it expects a parameter that is expanded to a value (With `XYZ` as described above: `ff_ftp XYZ`).

